## 2) Implemented Core Systems (Working)

## A. Authentication + Access
- Email/password login
- Unique ID + PIN login
- OTP based signup flow
- Password reset flow
- JWT token based session
- Role-based access (user, manager, admin, super-admin)
- Protected APIs + protected admin/dashboard access

User value:
- secure onboarding
- fast login options
- role-wise correct feature access

## B. Plans, Billing, Subscription
- **Manage Plans (Super Admin ŌåÆ Billing & Config):** `priceMonthly` / `priceYearly` MongoDB `Plan` docs ŌĆö **single source of truth** for marketing + Razorpay (`GET /api/subscriptions/plans`, `lib/planPricing.ts`)
- Tiers: **Free**, **Starter** (default **$3/mo**), **Pro** (default **$15/mo**), **Enterprise**, **Custom** ŌĆö display amounts admin-configurable
- Checkout + payment verification uses **DB plan prices** (not hardcoded constants only; fallback if plan row missing)
- **Currency correctness:** DB plan prices are stored/treated as **USD**; signup/checkout now converts **USD ŌåÆ selected locale currency** (from `LocaleContext`) and sends Razorpay order with the correct `amount` + `currency` (minor units handling: paise/cents; JPY/JR-style 0-decimals supported)
- **Signup billing consistency:** `prepare-signup` stores `PendingUser.currency` + country; `verify-and-pay` creates Razorpay order using that currency and stores USD + Razorpay metadata on `PendingUser`, so **billingHistory + receipt** use the charged amount/currency (no USD/INR mismatch)
- Subscription status and usage APIs; plan ŌåÆ role mapping (e.g. Pro ŌåÆ manager, Enterprise ŌåÆ admin; Starter ŌåÆ user)
- Invoice/receipt related flows

User value:
- same prices on landing, `/pricing`, signup, and checkout (and the charged amount matches the selected currency)
- clear plan upgrade path; controlled usage by plan

## C. Video Analysis System
- Multi-source analysis flows:
  - YouTube
